{"name":"LinearProgramming","type":"function","version":2,"rank":942,"url":"http://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/LinearProgramming.html","usage":"<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*]</b> finds a vector *x* that minimizes the quantity *c*.*x* subject to the constraints *m*.*x*≥*b* and *x*≥0. \n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,{{*b*₁,*s*₁},{*b*₂,*s*₂},…}]</b> finds a vector *x* that minimizes *c*.*x* subject to *x*≥0 and linear constraints specified by the matrix *m* and the pairs {*bᵢ*,*sᵢ*}. For each row *mᵢ* of *m*, the corresponding constraint is *mᵢ*.*x*≥*bᵢ* if *sᵢ*==1, or *mᵢ*.*x*==*bᵢ* if *sᵢ*==0, or *mᵢ*.*x*≤*bᵢ* if *sᵢ*==\\-1. \n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*,*l*]</b> minimizes *c*.*x* subject to the constraints specified by *m* and *b* and *x*≥*l*. \n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*,{*l*₁,*l*₂,…}]</b> minimizes *c*.*x* subject to the constraints specified by *m* and *b* and *xᵢ*≥*lᵢ*. \n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*,{{*l*₁,*u*₁},{*l*₂,*u*₂},…}]</b> minimizes *c*.*x* subject to the constraints specified by *m* and *b* and *lᵢ*≤*xᵢ*≤*uᵢ*. \n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*,*lu*,*dom*]</b> takes the elements of *x* to be in the domain *dom*, either Reals or Integers.\n\n---\n<b>LinearProgramming[*c*,*m*,*b*,*lu*,{*dom*₁,*dom*₂,…}]</b> takes *xᵢ* to be in the domain *domᵢ*."}

{"name":"ListConvolve","type":"function","version":4,"rank":1111,"url":"http://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/ListConvolve.html","usage":"<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*]</b> forms the convolution of the kernel *ker* with *list*. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,*k*]</b> forms the cyclic convolution in which the *k*ᵗʰ element of *ker* is aligned with each element in *list*. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,{*kL*,*kR*}]</b> forms the cyclic convolution whose first element contains *list*[[1]]*ker*[[*kL*]] and whose last element contains *list*[[\\-1]]*ker*[[*kR*]]. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,*klist*,*p*]</b> forms the convolution in which *list* is padded at each end with repetitions of the element *p*. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,*klist*,{*p*₁,*p*₂,…}]</b> forms the convolution in which *list* is padded at each end with cyclic repetitions of the *pᵢ*. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,*klist*,*padding*,*g*,*h*]</b> forms a generalized convolution in which *g* is used in place of Times and *h* in place of Plus. \n\n---\n<b>ListConvolve[*ker*,*list*,*klist*,*padding*,*g*,*h*,*lev*]</b> forms a convolution using elements at level *lev* in *ker* and *list*. "}
